					<p>A little awareness goes a long way.</p>
					<ul>
						<li><strong>Overthinking Formality:</strong> Tashi Delek is appropriate in almost all situations.</li>
						<li><strong>Mispronouncing "Delek":</strong> Avoid saying "de-LEK." The emphasis is on the first syllable: "DEH-lek."</li>
						<li><strong>Forgetting Body Language:</strong> A slight bow, a smile, or bringing your hands together near your chest (a subtle namaste) adds great respect.</li>
						<li><strong>Using "Kaleh pheb" incorrectly:</strong> Remember, you say "Kaleh pheb" to the person leaving, and "Kaleh shu" if you are the one leaving.</li>
					</ul>

